"favorite_intro" : "This feature allows you to create your own library of favorite lists. You can create Favorite Lists for Auricular, Diagnosis, Formulas, Herbs, Points, and Master Tung.

First, select the area where you will create a list. Then select the "Add New Favorite List" item. You will be prompted for a list name. After you enter a name, click Save, and proceed to selecting the items you want in your list.

You can use these favorite lists for limiting general display or in the Quiz Yourself section. Selection of the "lists to use" is managed by the menu item "Favorites to Use"."

"favorite_sharing" : "Once you have selected one or more "Favorite Lists to Use" you can share these lists with colleagues by clicking on Menu, then selecting the "Post" menu-item to upload your list(s) for sharing. Only lists defined on this screen can be shared.

When you click on the "Post" menu item, you will be prompted to provide a keyword of your own choosing. This keyword will be an identifier for your Favorite Lists. You can share the keyword with any of your colleagues to allow them to "Grab" your shared lists which are then added to their Favorites Lists library.

To 'Grab' a colleague's Favorites Lists, click on Menu, then click on the "Grab" menu item. When you click on the "Grab" menu item, you will be prompted to provide the keyword your colleague gave you to retrieve his or her lists.

Retrieved lists are immediately placed in your Favorites Lists library for immediate use."

"favorite_to_use_text" : "The "Favorites to Use" menu item, on the main TCM Clinic Aid screen, allows you to specify which previously defined "Favorites Lists" you would like to use to override the default list of specific items (e.g., Auricular, Diagnosis, Herbs, Formulas, Points, and Master Tung).

You can also create Favorite Lists from the "Favorites to Use" screen by clicking on Menu, then click on and "Create" icon.

Once you have defined your Favorites Lists, you can select them by selecting the "Favorites to Use" option from the main menu and:

	1. Select a category,

	2. Scroll to the list you want to use,

	3. The list you selected should appear in the section below the tumbler.

Please note: once you select a favorite list only the items you have specified will be viewable when you drill-down (e.g., into Herbs, Points, etc) or when performing a search.

To return to the system default data, just select "- Not In Use -" for each of the categories.

To activate your Favorites Lists, go to the Main Screen and click on the Star icon. Now, whenever you view Auricular, Diagnosis, Herbs, Formulas, Points, and/or Master Tung, only those items you selected for your lists will be available for display. When you want to deactivate your Favorites Lists, go to the Main Screen and click on the Badge icon.

As long as a favorite list is selected for an area, it will be used during list display. For example, if you create a favorite herb list called HerbsToStudy, and it contains 10 herbs, when you select HerbsToStudy as the Favorite List to use for herbs, only these 10 herbs will display when you drill down into the Herb data."

"xl_quiz_intro" : "This section allows you to quiz yourself on different aspects of Auricular, Diagnosis, Herbs, Formulas, Points, Pulses, and Tongue Diagnosis.

To start, press the "Begin" button.

From the 'Select Quiz' screen choose one of the areas for testing.

Next, select the type of quiz you want to run from the 'Open for Quizzes' dropdown.

Click 'Next' and select the specific category to be quizzed on.

Finally, click 'Next' to begin the quiz.

When you're done testing yourself, click on 'History' to review your results and review those items you missed."

playstore_details.title: Tcm Clinic Aid Trial
playstore_details.description:
Note: This trial version of TCM Clinic Aid allows the user to use the app 20 times.

TCM Clinic Aid is a reference guide for practitioners and students of Traditional Chinese Medicine (Acupuncturist and Herbalist). It should not be used to diagnose ailments or diseases. Diagnosis should be done by a licensed Acupuncturist and Herbalist.

KEY FEATURES:

Search our relational database for:
1. Acupuncture and Auricular points,
- Includes images of Acupuncture points.
- Includes Chinese characters and pinyin with tonemarks for all Acupuncture points.
- Includes images of Auricular points.
2. Individual Herbs and Herbal Formulas,
- Includes images of individual herbs.
- Includes Chinese characters and pinyin with tonemarks for all Herbs and Herbal Formulas.
3. Diagnosis Etiologies,
4. Search by symptoms and indications.
5. You can also search for a specific diagnosis, formulas, herbs, and points using the following:
a. Diagnosis etiologies searched by pathology name, i.e., 'Liver Yang Rising', suggested points, or suggested formulas,
b. Formula names searched by pinyin, english name, ingredients, western uses (western ailments it can treat),
c. Herb names searched by pinyin, english or botanical (latin),
d. Points searched by common name, i.e., 'LI4'.

Browse or "drill down" through 1600+ points, herbs, formulas and diagnosis etiology.

User modification/editing of auricular, diagnosis, herbs, formulas and points.

The following components are also included:
1. Master Tung Points.
2. Wrist/Ankle Acupuncture.
3. Quiz Yourself.
4. Pulse Diagnosis
